HEADWORD: Ondograph
<hw>On"do*graph</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>onde</ets> wave, L. <ets>unda</ets> + <ets>-graph</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>An instrument for autographically recording the
wave forms of varying currents, esp. rapidly varying alternating
currents.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

